SIMPLE: zirconia
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Zirconia
<hw>Zir*co"ni*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>The oxide of zirconium (<chform>ZrO2</chform>),
obtained as a white powder, and possessing both acid and basic
properties. On account of its infusibility, and brilliant luminosity
when incandescent, it is used as an ingredient of sticks for the
Drummond light.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>cubic zirconia</b></col>. <cd>A colorless form of
zirconia similar in appearance and refractivity to diamond, and used as
a substitute for diamonds in inexpensive jewelry; -- also known by the
acronym <altname>CZ</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Zirconic</ent>⟦br⟧
